abstract: U.S. House Democrats on Wednesday unveiled a proposed $760 billion infrastructure spending bill over five years that aims to rebuild sagging roads and bridges and reduce carbon pollution.
snippet: U.S. House Democrats on Wednesday unveiled a proposed $760 billion infrastructure spending bill over five years that aims to rebuild sagging roads and bridges and reduce carbon pollution.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. House Democrats on Wednesday unveiled a proposed $760 billion infrastructure spending bill over five years that aims to rebuild sagging roads and bridges and reduce carbon pollution.
headline_main: U.S. House Democrats Call for $760 Billion in Infrastructure Spending Over Five Years
headline_print_headline: U.S. House Democrats Call for $760 Billion in Infrastructure Spending Over Five Years

abstract: Naama Issachar had been sentenced to seven and a half years in prison for a small amount of marijuana. The case was linked to the American extradition of a Russian man.
snippet: Naama Issachar had been sentenced to seven and a half years in prison for a small amount of marijuana. The case was linked to the American extradition of a Russian man.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — An American-Israeli woman was pardoned on Wednesday, months after her severe punishment on charges of having a small amount of marijuana had made her an unwitting pawn in a geopolitical game.

abstract: The courts have declared, Representative Adam B. Schiff said of the president, “You’re not a king.”
snippet: The courts have declared, Representative Adam B. Schiff said of the president, “You’re not a king.”
lead_paragraph: Pushing back on President Trump’s defense team’s expansive view of his presidential prerogatives, Representative Adam B. Schiff of California, the chairman of the House Intelligence Committee and the lead impeachment manager, accused Mr. Trump of being “a president who identifies the state as being himself.”

abstract: Abu Dis, the town earmarked for the Palestinian capital in U.S. President Donald Trump's Middle East peace plan, lies a short distance to the east of Jerusalem's walled Old City.
snippet: Abu Dis, the town earmarked for the Palestinian capital in U.S. President Donald Trump's Middle East peace plan, lies a short distance to the east of Jerusalem's walled Old City.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — Abu Dis, the town earmarked for the Palestinian capital in U.S. President Donald Trump's Middle East peace plan, lies a short distance to the east of Jerusalem's walled Old City.
headline_main: Abu Dis, an Unlikely Capital for a Future Palestinian State
headline_print_headline: Abu Dis, an Unlikely Capital for a Future Palestinian State

abstract: U.S. authorities on Wednesday announced the discovery of the longest smuggling tunnel ever found on the Southwest border, stretching more than three-quarters of a mile from an industrial site in Tijuana, Mexico, to the San Diego area.
snippet: U.S. authorities on Wednesday announced the discovery of the longest smuggling tunnel ever found on the Southwest border, stretching more than three-quarters of a mile from an industrial site in Tijuana, Mexico, to the San Diego area.
lead_paragraph: SAN DIEGO — U.S. authorities on Wednesday announced the discovery of the longest smuggling tunnel ever found on the Southwest border, stretching more than three-quarters of a mile from an industrial site in Tijuana, Mexico, to the San Diego area.
headline_main: Authorities Find Longest Southwest Border Smuggling Tunnel
headline_print_headline: Authorities Find Longest Southwest Border Smuggling Tunnel

abstract: With more than 15,000 people killed by gun violence in the United States last year - not counting suicides - Democrats running for their party's presidential nomination are pointing to inaction in Washington as evidence they should be chosen to run against Republican President Donald Trump.
snippet: With more than 15,000 people killed by gun violence in the United States last year - not counting suicides - Democrats running for their party's presidential nomination are pointing to inaction in Washington as evidence they should be chosen to ru...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - With more than 15,000 people killed by gun violence in the United States last year - not counting suicides - Democrats running for their party's presidential nomination are pointing to inaction in Washington as evidence they should be chosen to run against Republican President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Background Checks and Bump Stock Bans: 2020 Democrats on Gun Control
headline_print_headline: Background Checks and Bump Stock Bans: 2020 Democrats on Gun Control

abstract: A special effort launched this week is promoting the idea of news literacy education to help the public, particularly young people who have grown up with social media, learn to track down trustworthy information.
snippet: A special effort launched this week is promoting the idea of news literacy education to help the public, particularly young people who have grown up with social media, learn to track down trustworthy information.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — A special effort launched this week is promoting the idea of news literacy education to help the public, particularly young people who have grown up with social media, learn to track down trustworthy information.
headline_main: Groups Promoting News Literacy to Combat Misinformation
headline_print_headline: Groups Promoting News Literacy to Combat Misinformation

abstract: Senators passed notes and appeared to be drafting questions on the fly.
snippet: Senators passed notes and appeared to be drafting questions on the fly.
lead_paragraph: The ability to ask questions — albeit only in writing — brought a new dynamic to the floor. Senators passed notes and appeared to be drafting questions on the fly, based on previous questions and the responses from President Trump’s lawyers and the Democratic House managers.
headline_main: Impeachment questions liven up the Senate chamber.
